8 SENATE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 16, L.D. 117, “An Act to Provide Funding for
9 Sexual Assault Services”
10 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
11 following:
12 'Sec. 1. Community-based services; domestic violence and sexual assault.
13 Notwithstanding any provision of Public Law 2025, chapter 388 to the contrary, any unused
14 balances of the one-time funding of $3,000,000 in fiscal year 2025-26 and one-time funding
15 of $3,000,000 in fiscal year 2026-27 appropriated to the Department of Health and Human
16 Services, Purchased Social Services program under Public Law 2025, chapter 388, Part A
17 to replace current and anticipated reductions in grants to the department under the federal
18 victim assistance formula grant program administered by the United States Department of
19 Justice, Office of Justice Programs, Office for Victims of Crime pursuant to the federal
20 Victims of Crime Act of 1984 not needed for that purpose must be disbursed in equal
21 amounts to a statewide coalition of domestic violence resource centers and to a statewide
22 coalition of sexual assault support centers to support community-based services. The
23 Department of Health and Human Services shall identify any unused balance as of March
24 30th of each year to be disbursed pursuant to this section.'
25 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
26 number to read consecutively.
27 SUMMARY
